-- Gruebel Says Credit Suisse Has Too Many Workers, Finanz Reports
-- B y   C o r i n n e   G r e t l e r
-- 2012-04-14T08:44:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-14/gruebel-says-credit-suisse-has-too-many-workers-finanz-reports.html
Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  employs
3,000 to 5,000 too many workers in its investment banking unit
considering revenue potential, former  UBS AG (UBSN)  Chief Executive
Officer Oswald Gruebel told  Finanz & Wirtschaft  in an interview.  Gruebel also said future management of major Swiss banks
will be about shrinking balance sheets rather than creating
growth, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Corinne Gretler in Zurich at +41-44-224-4100 or
 cgretler1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
